20 SUMMARY
2211 This bill addresses certain recommendations from the Transforming Interpreting Maine
2222 (TIME) needs assessment report issued by the Department of Health and Human Services
2233 in 2024 in the wake of the October 2023 Lewiston shooting. The bill authorizes an
2244 exemption to American Sign Language interpreter licensure during emergencies, creates a
2255 broader educational pathway to licensure and extends the period of conditional licensure
2266 from 4 to 5 years, with a 6th year granted in cases of extreme hardship.
